{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/a-step-by-step-tutorial-using-k-means-to-extract-image-color-themes-43e04808b2be", "time": 1683017900.0505338, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/a-step-by-step-tutorial-using-k-means-to-extract-image-color-themes-43e04808b2be/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "A step-by-step tutorial using K-means to extract image color themes | by Viola Mao | Towards Data Science", "h1": "A step-by-step tutorial using K-means to extract image color themes", "description": "Many people are struggling when choosing Powerpoint theme colors. We are not color experts and the default color palette has been used in many presentations. More importantly, we want something that\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/violamao/", "anchor_text": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/violamao/", "paragraph_index": 18}], "all_paragraphs": ["Many people are struggling when choosing Powerpoint theme colors. We are not color experts and the default color palette has been used in many presentations.", "More importantly, we want something that is natural, and comfortable. There are articles about fashion designers using Nature\u2019s color for their inspiration. We could, as well, use the natural color for our data visualizations. Overall, nature\u2019s color scheme always provides the most beautiful color match.", "In this article, I will use K-means for the RGB values clustering to find the color themes through nature images.", "2. Use K-means to find the dominant colors", "There are multiple ways to detect RGB values in Python. Here we use imread within library matplotlib.", "In imread\u2019s view, images are consisted by 3 layers of R, G, B values and imread will return an M*N*3 array with M*N as the image\u2019s size (pixels) and 3 is for the R, G, B three layers.", "There are other ways to show the R, G, B channels of this image:", "Before we apply K-means to find the dominant colors, we need:", "Convert the M*N*3 array to 3 one-dimensional lists and put them into a dataframe for further processing.", "Next, similar to how we process data in the other machine learning projects, the data elements need to be standardized or whiten.", "We will use kmeans from scipy for the data cluster. Here, we aim to find 5 main colors from that image.", "kmeans returns two values cluster_centers and distortions. For our purpose, only cluster_centers value is used.", "The cluster_centers consist of standardized values that will need to restore to the real R, G, B to retrieve the colors.", "imshow could show image either within 0 to 1 float or 0 to 255 int. So we use int() to return the integer values for each cluster center.", "In this tutorial, we use matplotlib and scipy to extract theme colors with K-means. Whenever you are bored with the default Powerpoint color palette, try to use this method to find other themes to inspire you :).", "Some other examples for your references:", "I like Machine Learning as I believe it can truly help our daily life. Please connect with me through LinkedIn:", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "Data is richer than you think! https://www.linkedin.com/in/violamao/"], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F43e04808b2be&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fa-step-by-step-tutorial-using-k-means-to-extract-image-color-themes-43e04808b2be&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fa-step-by-step-tutorial-using-k-means-to-extract-image-color-themes-43e04808b2be&source=post_